SIMPLE: yowl
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yowl
<hw>Yowl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Yawl</er>,
<pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To utter a loud, long, and mournful cry, as
a dog; to howl; to yell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yowl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Yowl
<hw>Yowl</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A loud, protracted, and mournful cry,
as that of a dog; a howl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yowley</ent>⟦br⟧
